110
00:10:55,864 --> 00:11:01,267
[SPEAKER_02]: The intent and purpose, this section regulates the removal of trees on private property in the city of Medford.

111
00:11:01,687 --> 00:11:09,311
[SPEAKER_02]: A mature tree canopy maintains the natural beauty of Medford for all to enjoy today and in the future generations and protects the community in critically important ways.

112
00:11:09,891 --> 00:11:14,714
[SPEAKER_02]: It reduces energy consumption and ambient summertime temperatures, air pollution, flooding, and soil erosion.

113
00:11:15,234 --> 00:11:18,336
[SPEAKER_02]: It provides privacy, absorbs noise, and boosts mental health.

114
00:11:18,416 --> 00:11:21,277
[SPEAKER_02]: It supports wildlife and increases resilience to climate change.

115
00:11:21,637 --> 00:11:25,079
[SPEAKER_02]: Protecting the city's tree canopy is thus an essential community function.

116
00:11:25,821 --> 00:11:36,729
[SPEAKER_02]: And I do want to say there's been a lot of people who have helped to write this first draft that is now being edited as well, not the least of which Trees Medford, as well as folks on the Energy and Environment Committee as well.

117
00:11:37,289 --> 00:11:44,474
[SPEAKER_02]: So under Caliper, we just have the update of diameter of a tree trunk in inches is measured 12 inches above the ground for trees.

118
00:11:45,112 --> 00:11:49,615
[SPEAKER_02]: up to and including a 10-inch diameter and 24 inches above the ground for larger trees.

119
00:11:50,316 --> 00:12:03,565
[SPEAKER_02]: The code enforcement officer is defined as the building commissioner or their designee, and construction permit is defined as a building permit issued by the building department, allowing construction, demolition, or renovation of buildings and structures on a parcel of land.

120
00:12:06,607 --> 00:12:11,490
[SPEAKER_02]: And then going into the definition for construction, any activity which affects trees, tree root zones,

121
00:12:12,084 --> 00:12:29,516
[SPEAKER_02]: or is within the drip line and that requires a building permit or trench permit, including driveways, retaining walls, solar installation where trees are removed, site work on foundations, underground utilities, excavation, grading, and paving construction or alteration of a structure or structure where the drip zone of a tree would be affected.

122
00:12:30,017 --> 00:12:33,099
[SPEAKER_02]: Any vegetation within five feet of a structure is excluded.

123
00:12:34,646 --> 00:12:43,492
[SPEAKER_02]: I'm going to drip line, which is a vertical line running through the outermost portion of the crown of a tree where the branches are five inches or greater and extending to the ground.

124
00:12:45,554 --> 00:12:57,322
[SPEAKER_02]: Pruning has been added to be defined as the act of removing, trimming, or looping any portion of a tree up to a maximum of 50% of branches greater than five inches in diameter that is overgrown or possesses a risk to persons or structures.

125
00:12:57,943 --> 00:13:03,927
[SPEAKER_02]: Removal is the act of removing a tree, which includes removal of the stump by pulling from the earth or grinding it to a level below grade

126
00:13:04,481 --> 00:13:04,741
[SPEAKER_02]: safe.

127
00:13:05,962 --> 00:13:15,149
[SPEAKER_02]: Replacement trees are trees planted or relocated by or on behalf of the resident owner or contractor to mitigate approved tree removal which are a minimum of three inch caliper.

128
00:13:15,789 --> 00:13:24,936
[SPEAKER_02]: Resident owner is identified as the legal owner of a property subject to this section who primarily resides at the property in which trees are disturbed for more than six months in a calendar year.

129
00:13:26,838 --> 00:13:31,261
[SPEAKER_02]: Tree protection replacement and mitigation plan is a plan submitted to the building commissioner or designee

130
00:13:31,657 --> 00:13:37,943
[SPEAKER_02]: for approval prior to the commencement of demolition and or construction on a property which trees defined in this section are located.

131
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:46,030
[SPEAKER_02]: Tree removal permit is a permit issued by the building department for removal of trees based on the appropriate application process on privately owned property.

132
00:13:47,271 --> 00:13:55,559
[SPEAKER_02]: Undeveloped land is defined as a parcel of land or portion thereof that has remained undisturbed from construction activity or maintenance for more than 15 years.

133
00:13:56,295 --> 00:14:01,459
[SPEAKER_02]: Applicability, the provisions of this section shall apply to the following activity on privately owned land.

134
00:14:02,119 --> 00:14:06,302
[SPEAKER_02]: Removal of any tree with a caliper of 10 inches or greater at breast height for any reason.

135
00:14:06,862 --> 00:14:14,748
[SPEAKER_02]: Construction, alteration, and demolition of a structure, parcel, accessory building, retaining wall, fence, or other structure where the removal of trees is necessary.

136
00:14:15,388 --> 00:14:22,653
[SPEAKER_02]: Alteration of any portion of a lot or parcel for the purposes of expanding activity area or cleared open space for leisure outdoor activity space.

137
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:27,669
[SPEAKER_02]: Removal of any tree 10 inches or greater in diameter at breast height or portion thereof.

138
00:14:29,530 --> 00:14:32,112
[SPEAKER_02]: And going to a schedule for mitigation and tree replacement.

139
00:14:32,152 --> 00:14:35,493
[SPEAKER_02]: Mitigation and tree replacement shall be in accordance with the following schedule.

140
00:14:36,074 --> 00:14:41,797
[SPEAKER_02]: Removal of one tree of 10 to 15 inches equals two trees of three-inch caliper.

141
00:14:42,277 --> 00:14:46,600
[SPEAKER_02]: Removal of one tree of 15 to 30 inches equals three trees of three-inch caliper.

142
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:50,922
[SPEAKER_02]: Removal of one tree 30 inches and above equals four trees of three-inch caliper.

143
00:14:51,746 --> 00:14:57,809
[SPEAKER_02]: Removal of multiple trees of any size or greater listed above are subject to a fee in accordance with the following schedule.

144
00:14:58,309 --> 00:15:03,592
[SPEAKER_02]: The total clearing of a parcel of land of up to 7,000 square feet is a $1,000 payment to the True Mitigation Fund.

145
00:15:04,072 --> 00:15:10,355
[SPEAKER_02]: The total clearing of a parcel of obtaining 7,000 to 20,000 square feet is a 2,500 payment to the True Mitigation Fund.

146
00:15:10,995 --> 00:15:17,119
[SPEAKER_02]: And more than 20,000 square feet of total lot clearing is subject to slight plan review by the CDB in accordance with Chapter 94, Section 94-11.7.

147
00:15:20,906 --> 00:15:27,714
[SPEAKER_02]: Resident owners must apply for a permit to remove trees from the property in which they reside for purposes of maintaining conditions near any structure.

148
00:15:28,214 --> 00:15:32,599
[SPEAKER_02]: Protected trees, as defined by this section, are subject to review and approval from the tree warden.

149
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:41,870
[SPEAKER_02]: If, in the opinion of the tree warden, that the trees to be removed are significant, they shall refer the proposed tree cutting removal to the Tree Preservation Committee.

150
00:15:42,678 --> 00:15:52,083
[SPEAKER_02]: Tree removal activity exempt from this section is a tree that poses an imminent risk of falling branches, rotted trunk base, or other indicators of failure as determined by a certified arborist.

151
00:15:52,743 --> 00:16:03,209
[SPEAKER_02]: Removal of any tree or portion thereof for purposes of gathering sunlight for photovoltaic solar panel systems or arrays, trees damaged by storms, or other natural causes.

152
00:16:04,373 --> 00:16:16,636
[SPEAKER_02]: protective and significant trees, trees that are 75 years or older as determined by a certified arborist or the tree warden shall be inventoried and preserved to the extent feasible, whether by resident owner or contractor approving the property.

153
00:16:17,275 --> 00:16:23,740
[SPEAKER_02]: If in the determination of the tree warrant, a tree should be preserved, the tree warrant shall refer the applicant to the tree committee for a public hearing.

154
